fr.ensimag.deca

Class DecacCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ensimag.deca.DecacCompiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Boolean>

    public class DecacCompiler
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.concurrent.Callable<java.lang.Boolean>
    Decac compiler instance. This class is to be instantiated once per source file to be compiled. It contains the meta-data used for compiling (source file name, compilation options) and the necessary utilities for compilation (symbol tables, abstract representation of target file, ...). It contains several objects specialized for different tasks. Delegate methods are used to simplify the code of the caller (e.g. call compiler.addInstruction() instead of compiler.getProgram().addInstruction()).
    Author:
    gl07

        private boolean doCompile(java.lang.String sourceName,
                          java.lang.String destName,
                          java.io.PrintStream out,

                   throws DecacFatalError,
                          LocationException
        Internal function that does the job of compiling (i.e. calling lexer, verification and code generation).
        Parameters:
        sourceName - name of the source (deca) file
        destName - name of the destination (assembly) file
        out - stream to use for standard output (output of decac -p)
        err - stream to use to display compilation errors
        Returns:
        true on error
        Throws:
        DecacFatalError
        LocationException

      • doLexingAndParsing

        protected AbstractProgram doLexingAndParsing(java.lang.String sourceName,
                                             java.io.PrintStream err)
                                      throws DecacFatalError,
                                             DecacInternalError
        Build and call the lexer and parser to build the primitive abstract syntax tree.
        Parameters:
        sourceName - Name of the file to parse
        err - Stream to send error messages to
        Returns:
        the abstract syntax tree
        Throws:
        DecacFatalError - When an error prevented opening the source file
        DecacInternalError - When an inconsistency was detected in the compiler.
        LocationException - When a compilation error (incorrect program) occurs.
